{"cursor":"2630","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"A 'convention center' (American English, 'conference centre' outside the USA) is\na large building that is designed to hold a convention, where individuals and\ngroups gather to promote and share common interests. Convention centers\ntypically offer sufficient floor area to accommodate several thousand attendees.\nVery large venues, suitable for major trade shows, are sometimes known as\n'exhibition centres'. Convention centers typically have at least one auditorium\nand may also contain concert halls, lecture halls, meeting rooms, and conference\nrooms. Some large resort area hotels include a convention center.\n","linknr":145,"url":"Convention_center","recorded":1362689489,"links":36,"instances":["meeting"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Convention centers|"],"headings":["Gallery","See also"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/00/Yarmarka.jpg/120px-Yarmarka.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/49/PICC.jpg/120px-PICC.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/87/Nm_toronto_metro_toronto_convention_centre.jpg/120px-Nm_toronto_metro_toronto_convention_centre.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a3/Salon_Chichen_Itza_in_Siglo_XXI_Convention_Centre%2C_M%C3%A9rida%2C_Mexico.JPG/120px-Salon_Chichen_Itza_in_Siglo_XXI_Convention_Centre%2C_M%C3%A9rida%2C_Mexico.JPG","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8f/20070110_McCormick_Place_%282%29.JPG/120px-20070110_McCormick_Place_%282%29.JPG","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a1/Prins_Bernhard_Hoeve_-_2nd_entrance.jpg/120px-Prins_Bernhard_Hoeve_-_2nd_entrance.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/15/Sandiegoconventioncenterfront.jpg/120px-Sandiegoconventioncenterfront.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9d/Pragati_Maidan%2C_Hall_6.JPG/120px-Pragati_Maidan%2C_Hall_6.JPG","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9b/David_L._Lawren